    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"老头儿 occupies a middle ground between formal and disrespectful. While more casual\nthan 老人 (elderly person), it's generally not considered rude when used appropriately. In Chinese\nculture, it can express familiarity and even affection, though context matters greatly for\nappropriateness."}],"type":"paragraph"}
